---
// Static editorial content for FundedNext Futures
// Supports multiple sections via the `section` prop
interface Props {
  section: string;
  fallbackBody?: string;
}
const { section, fallbackBody } = Astro.props;
---

{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{/* CHALLENGES SECTION                                                  */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "challenges" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <!-- Overview -->
  <p class="mb-4">
    FundedNext Futures offers three challenge models &mdash; <strong>Rapid</strong>, <strong>Legacy</strong>, and <strong>Bolt</strong> &mdash; each designed for CME futures traders with different risk profiles and trading styles. There are no monthly fees or activation charges, and challenge fees start from <strong>$129</strong>. You can use our exclusive FundedNext promo code <strong>PF</strong> at checkout for discounted fees.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    All accounts operate in a <strong>simulated trading environment</strong> using demo accounts with real CME pricing. The models differ in profit targets, loss limits, and risk structure, giving traders the flexibility to choose a program that matches their approach.
  </p>

  <!-- Simulated Environment Callout -->
  <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-4 mb-8">
    <p class="text-sm font-bold text-amber-900 mb-1">Simulated Trading Environment</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-amber-800">
      FundedNext Futures provides simulated trading challenges using demo accounts. While the environment uses real CME pricing and market conditions, all execution occurs on simulated accounts rather than live exchange accounts.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── Rapid Challenge Table ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Rapid Challenge</h3>
  <p class="mb-3">
    The Rapid model uses trailing loss limits and offers account sizes of $25K, $50K, and $100K.
  </p>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm whitespace-nowrap">
      <thead class="bg-slate-800 text-xs font-semibold text-white uppercase tracking-wide">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Attribute</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$25,000</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$50,000</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$100,000</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Profit Target</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$1,500</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$3,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$5,000</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Trailing Loss Limit</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$1,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$2,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$2,500</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Loss Limit Type</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900" colspan="3">Trailing</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── Legacy Challenge Table ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Legacy Challenge</h3>
  <p class="mb-3">
    The Legacy model also uses trailing loss limits and is available in $25K, $50K, and $100K account sizes.
  </p>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm whitespace-nowrap">
      <thead class="bg-slate-800 text-xs font-semibold text-white uppercase tracking-wide">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Attribute</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$25,000</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$50,000</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$100,000</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Profit Target</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$1,250</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$2,500</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$6,000</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Trailing Loss Limit</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$1,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$2,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$3,000</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Loss Limit Type</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900" colspan="3">Trailing</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── Bolt Challenge Table ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Bolt Challenge</h3>
  <p class="mb-3">
    The Bolt model is available as a $50K account and uses a fixed daily aggregate loss limit combined with a trailing loss limit.
  </p>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm whitespace-nowrap">
      <thead class="bg-slate-800 text-xs font-semibold text-white uppercase tracking-wide">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Attribute</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$50,000</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Profit Target</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$3,000</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Daily Aggregate Loss Limit</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$1,000</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Trailing Loss Limit</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">$2,000</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Key Specs -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-2 mb-6">
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Challenge Models</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">Rapid, Legacy, Bolt</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Account Type</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">Simulated (Demo)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Activation Fee</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-teal-600">$0</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Contract Types</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">Mini &amp; Micro</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Best Suited For -->
  <div class="rounded-xl bg-teal-50 border border-teal-200 p-4 mb-8">
    <p class="text-xs font-bold text-teal-800 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Suited For</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-teal-700">Futures traders who want a choice between multiple challenge models with different risk profiles. Rapid and Legacy suit traders who prefer trailing loss limits, while Bolt offers a tighter daily aggregate loss structure.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- CHALLENGE DETAILS                                               -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">How the Challenges Work</h3>

  <p class="mb-3">
    To pass a FundedNext Futures challenge, you need to reach the profit target for your chosen model while staying within the loss limits. Rapid and Legacy both use trailing loss limits that adjust based on your account performance. Bolt adds a fixed daily aggregate loss limit on top of the trailing loss limit.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-3">
    You can trade both mini and micro contracts. Micros count as one-tenth of a mini, so if your cap is 3 mini contracts, you could instead trade up to 30 micros. This gives more flexibility over position sizing, especially for smaller accounts.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    All positions must be closed by end of session &mdash; no overnight holding is permitted. Automated trading (bots, EAs, HFT) is prohibited. Hedging across accounts and latency arbitrage are also not allowed.
  </p>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- TRADING RULES                                                   -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Futures Trading Rules</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">
    FundedNext has a detailed set of trading restrictions aimed at keeping the evaluation realistic. These rules apply during both the challenge and funded stages.
  </p>

  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-6">
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
      <thead class="bg-slate-50 text-xs font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Rule</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Details</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Automated Trading</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">Bots, EAs, and any form of automated execution are <span class="text-red-500 font-semibold">prohibited</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Scalping Limits</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">Excessive micro-scalping, HFT-style activity, and bracket trading that exploits fill behavior are not permitted</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Hedging</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">Cannot hedge across multiple accounts or use correlated instruments to reduce exposure artificially</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Latency Arbitrage</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">Taking advantage of price feed delays or simulated fills is not allowed</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">DCA &amp; Overleveraging</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">Adding to losing trades without clear structure is not allowed; position sizing must reflect controlled risk</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Price Limit Rule</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">If a contract moves within 2% of the CME price limit, trading that instrument must stop for the day</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Overnight Holding</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">All positions must be closed by end of session &mdash; <span class="text-red-500 font-semibold">no overnight trades</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Order Manipulation</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">Spoofing, layering, DOM manipulation, and wash trading are banned</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- SCALING PLAN                                                    -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Futures Account Scaling</h3>

  <p class="mb-3">
    When you pass a FundedNext Futures challenge and receive a funded account, you unlock contract scaling. This feature lets you trade more contracts as you grow your account balance.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    Scaling happens automatically based on your end-of-day (EOD) balance. As your profits increase, FundedNext Futures raises the number of contracts you're allowed to trade.
  </p>

  <!-- Verdict -->
  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-teal-500 bg-teal-50/60 px-5 py-4">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-800 mb-1">Verdict on Challenges and Rules</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      FundedNext Futures stands out by offering three distinct challenge models rather than a one-size-fits-all approach. Rapid and Legacy give traders trailing loss limits with different profit targets, while Bolt adds a tighter daily aggregate structure. The rules are clearly defined, and the simulated trading environment uses real CME pricing. All positions must be closed by end of session, and automated trading is prohibited.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>
)}

{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{/* SPREADS / COMMISSION FEES & PRICING SECTION                         */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "spreads" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <p class="mb-4">
    FundedNext Futures has a simple, upfront cost structure. You pay a one-time fee to enter the challenge, and there are <strong>no activation fees or monthly charges</strong> applied after the initial purchase.
  </p>

  <!-- Fee structure overview -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-2 mb-8">
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Activation Fee</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-teal-600">$0</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Monthly Fee</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-teal-600">$0</p>
