{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{/* MARKETS / FINANCIAL MARKETS & LEVERAGE SECTION                      */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "markets" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <p class="mb-4">
    FundedNext Futures gives traders access to a focused range of <strong>CME Group products</strong>, covering all the major futures asset classes: currencies, equity indices, metals, energy, and agriculture. The selection is built around high-volume markets that most traders already prioritize.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    Both mini and micro contract sizing are available, with micros counting as one-tenth of a mini.
  </p>

  <!-- Market Categories -->
  <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">

    <!-- Forex -->
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Forex Pairs</h3>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Major currency pairs are available through standard and micro contracts. This includes instruments like Euro FX, British Pound, and AUD/USD. It's a decent lineup if you are looking to take directional currency positions in a structured, exchange-based environment.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Indices -->
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Indices</h3>
      <p class="mb-3">
        FundedNext covers the big four US indices &mdash; <strong>S&amp;P 500, Nasdaq, Dow Jones, and Russell 2000</strong> &mdash; each with both mini and micro versions. These are among the most actively traded futures contracts globally and are ideal for intraday trading.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Metals -->
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Metals</h3>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Gold, silver, and copper are available, including micro contracts. These give you access to momentum and mean-reversion setups around macro news and commodities flows.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Energy -->
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Energy</h3>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Crude oil, natural gas, heating oil, and gasoline futures are included, with micro and mini crude contract options. Crude oil in particular is popular among futures traders due to its volatility and clean technical structure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Agriculture -->
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Agriculture &amp; Livestock</h3>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Corn, soybeans, wheat, and livestock futures like lean hogs and live cattle round out the list. These are niche markets, but good to have if you want to diversify around seasonal and fundamental catalysts.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- Contract Sizing -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Contract Sizing</h3>

  <p class="mb-6">
    All traders on FundedNext Futures are subject to contract limits based on account size. Micro contracts are 1/10th the size of mini contracts, and FundedNext treats them interchangeably using that ratio. Contract limits scale with account size and can increase further through the scaling plan as your balance grows.
  </p>

  <!-- Verdict -->
  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-teal-500 bg-teal-50/60 px-5 py-4">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-800 mb-1">Verdict on Markets</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      FundedNext Futures offers a streamlined but well-structured product lineup. It focuses on high-liquidity contracts that suit most trading styles, and includes both mini and micro options for flexible sizing. The mix of markets is strong enough to support everything from index scalping to energy trend trading. While it's not the widest selection in the prop industry, all the essential categories are covered.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>
)}

